  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Every child needs a good teacher (Mali)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One in four Malian children do not go to primary school at all (half a milion in total), and just over half complete primary education. Around 40% of them attend community schools where the teachers are rarely trained and are mostly unqualified. This pilot project will increase the skills of all 2,500 community teachers in S&#xE9;gou, one of eight Malian provinces, using a locally-developed &#x2018;competence framework&#x2019;. This will benefit 80,000 community school pupils, and aims to increase the number of children passing annual exams and completing primary school on time by 20%. The project will also tell parents, teachers and children about the framework, so they know what to expect of a &#x2018;good teacher&#x2019;.</narrative>
  </description>
